headline: Realtor.com® December Rent Report: Relief Skips Many Lower-Cost Renters
summary: Asking rents declined for the 29th consecutive month year over year in December, but the latest data show the easing is increasingly concentrated among higher-priced rentals, leaving many lower-cost renters with little relief. The median asking rent across the 50 largest U.S. metros was $1,689, down 0.7% from December 2024, according to the Realtor.com® December Rental Report.

headline: Is News Corp (NWSA) Fairly Priced After Realtor.com FlyAround Product Launch?
summary: If you are wondering whether News is genuinely good value at its recent price, it helps to start by comparing what the share price has done with how the company is being assessed on valuation.
